    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>RECOMMEND BANISHING EXECUTIVE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen DeMasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Gaming Enforcement Division recommends taking casino license away from Caesars Atlantic City president Gary DiBartolomeo, who has admitted to longstanding gambling problem and to lying about it (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Division of Gaming Enforcement last week recommended that the president of Caesars Atlantic City Hotel Casino, who has admitted to a longstanding gambling problem, lose his casino licenses, the first such recommendation to be made the 22 years of legal gambling in Atlantic City. The Casino Control Commission agreed to hold a hearing to consider the recommendation. A 65-page report said Gary DiBartolomeo, 45, lied to the division, gambled on at least 23 occasions when he had promised not to, and ran up $389,000 in debt in one 18-month period.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
